gemini.explanation: The system correctly identifies the critical safety risk of installing an uninsulated GDB housing outdoors. However, it fails on product selection by recommending the GDMI FLEX (cartridge/carbon housing) instead of the GDMI (bag filter housing). The user requested GDB (bag filters), and the direct insulated equivalent is GDMI, not GDMI FLEX. Additionally, GDMI FLEX has significantly lower airflow capacity for the same dimensions, which would violate the user's airflow requirement.

dimension_explanations.correctness: The system recommends GDMI FLEX (cartridges, PDF p.18) to replace GDB (bags, PDF p.8), which is the wrong product family; the correct insulated alternative is GDMI (PDF p.11).
dimension_explanations.completeness: It addresses the environment and material issues well but misses the correct product alternative.
dimension_explanations.safety: Correctly identifies the risk of condensation and corrosion for uninsulated housings outdoors.
dimension_explanations.reasoning_quality: The logic for blocking the GDB is technically sound (condensation risk), but the logic for recommending GDMI FLEX implies a misunderstanding of filter types.
dimension_explanations.constraint_adherence: Violates the airflow constraint: GDB 600x600 handles 3400 mÂ³/h (PDF p.9), while the recommended GDMI FLEX 600x600 only handles 1750 mÂ³/h (PDF p.18).
